# Counter App

A simple, responsive counter application that allows users to increment or decrement a value using interactive buttons. Built using HTML, Tailwind CSS, and vanilla JavaScript.

## 🚀 Features

- Minimal and clean user interface
- Responsive design using Tailwind CSS
- Functional increment and decrement buttons
- Font Awesome icons for visual clarity

## 📁 Project Structure
├── index.html # Main HTML page
├── index.js # JavaScript logic for the counter

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- HTML5
- Tailwind CSS (via CDN)
- Font Awesome Icons (via CDN)
- JavaScript (vanilla)

## 🔧 How to Run

1. Clone or download the repository.
2. Open the `index.html` file in any modern browser.
3. Click on the `+` or `–` icons to increase or decrease the counter.

## 📸 Preview

The UI features a central card with two buttons:
- ➖ (decrement): decreases the number
- ➕ (increment): increases the number

## 📌 Note

- No frameworks or build tools required — everything runs directly in the browser.
- Make sure you have internet access to load Tailwind and Font Awesome from the CDN.

